abstract: U.S. fuel card company FleetCor Technologies Inc charged customers hundreds of millions of dollars in hidden fees after promising to help them spend less on fuel, the Federal Trade Commission said on Friday.
snippet: U.S. fuel card company FleetCor Technologies Inc charged customers hundreds of millions of dollars in hidden fees after promising to help them spend less on fuel, the Federal Trade Commission said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. fuel card company FleetCor Technologies Inc charged customers hundreds of millions of dollars in hidden fees after promising to help them spend less on fuel, the Federal Trade Commission said on Friday.
headline_main: U.S. Accuses FleetCor of Charging Hundreds of Millions of Dollars in Hidden Fees
headline_print_headline: U.S. Accuses FleetCor of Charging Hundreds of Millions of Dollars in Hidden Fees

abstract: The European Union will insist on guarantees of a level-playing field in any agreement on future ties with Britain after Brexit, the chairman of EU leaders said on Friday.
snippet: The European Union will insist on guarantees of a level-playing field in any agreement on future ties with Britain after Brexit, the chairman of EU leaders said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Union will insist on guarantees of a level-playing field in any agreement on future ties with Britain after Brexit, the chairman of EU leaders said on Friday.
headline_main: Level Playing Field a Must for Future EU-UK Ties-EU's Michel
headline_print_headline: Level Playing Field a Must for Future EU-UK Ties-EU's Michel

snippet: Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar has argued for weeks that Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of a small Indiana city, doesn't have enough experience to be a serious contender for the Democratic nomination for president. As she heads into a 27-county tour  of ...
lead_paragraph: CENTERVILLE, Iowa — Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar has argued for weeks that Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of a small Indiana city, doesn't have enough experience to be a serious contender for the Democratic nomination for president. As she heads into a 27-county tour of Iowa, the lead-off caucus state, s he's seeing some payoff for bringing those frustrations fully into public view.
headline_main: Klobuchar Steps Up Hits on Buttigieg With Iowa Vote Looming
headline_print_headline: Klobuchar Steps Up Hits on Buttigieg With Iowa Vote Looming

abstract: The deal resolves allegations of anti-competitive behavior by the large hospital system in Northern California.
snippet: The deal resolves allegations of anti-competitive behavior by the large hospital system in Northern California.
lead_paragraph: Sutter Health, the large hospital system in Northern California, said Friday that it had agreed to pay $575 million to settle claims of anti-competitive behavior brought by the California state attorney general as well as unions and employers.

abstract: At stake is control of the country’s National Assembly, which is controlled by the opposition leader Juan Guaidó, who has accused President Nicolás Maduro of corruption.
snippet: At stake is control of the country’s National Assembly, which is controlled by the opposition leader Juan Guaidó, who has accused President Nicolás Maduro of corruption.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States accused President Nicolás Maduro of Venezuela on Friday of trying to rig a coming election for control of his country’s parliament, either by detaining opposition leaders or bribing lawmakers with up to $500,000 for each vote.

abstract: The Trump administration on Friday said it has finalized a decision to roll back a 2007 rule calling for energy-efficient light bulbs, a move that states including New York and California are challenging in the courts.
snippet: The Trump administration on Friday said it has finalized a decision to roll back a 2007 rule calling for energy-efficient light bulbs, a move that states including New York and California are challenging in the courts.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Friday said it has finalized a decision to roll back a 2007 rule calling for energy-efficient light bulbs, a move that states including New York and California are challenging in the courts.
headline_main: U.S. Rolls Back Standards on Energy Saving Light Bulbs
headline_print_headline: U.S. Rolls Back Standards on Energy Saving Light Bulbs

abstract: The highly anticipated movie "Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker" collected $40 million in U.S. and Canadian ticket sales on its opening night, the fifth-highest debut of all time, Walt Disney Co said on Friday.
snippet: The highly anticipated movie "Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker" collected $40 million in U.S. and Canadian ticket sales on its opening night, the fifth-highest debut of all time, Walt Disney Co said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The highly anticipated movie "Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker" collected $40 million in U.S. and Canadian ticket sales on its opening night, the fifth-highest debut of all time, Walt Disney Co said on Friday.
headline_main: 'Rise of Skywalker' Battles to $40 Million Domestic Opening Night
headline_print_headline: 'Rise of Skywalker' Battles to $40 Million Domestic Opening Night

abstract: A Mariah Carey Christmas classic hits No. 1 — finally. A look at an American slum. The case of the angry daughter. The decade in pictures and more.
snippet: A Mariah Carey Christmas classic hits No. 1 — finally. A look at an American slum. The case of the angry daughter. The decade in pictures and more.
lead_paragraph: Welcome to the weekend. We’ve had an impeachment (as if you didn’t know). There’s been some snow in New York and super hot temperatures in Australia. And there’s a big holiday coming up. Are you ready? However you celebrate — and even if you don’t — we wish you all the best.
